Table 8: Statistics of CICERO (Ghosal et al., 2022).

Table 11: The lexical similarity between answers and context also impact models' performance significantly. lowr 
and highr denote low rouge precision and high rouge precision groups respectively. R c and R i denote the average 
ROUGE score of correct and incorrect answers, respectively.

Table 13: An example of input, reference, and generated output triplets for the various groups of objective functions 
( ?4.2) from a dialogue D. PO, SCAO, CO, DO, and SO refers to the Primary Objectives, Single Correct Answer 
Objectives, Concept-Based Objectives, Denoising Objectives, and Sorting Based Objectives, respectively. The 
outputs are generated from the pretrained DIALECT model. The context placeholder x is the concatenation of the 
utterances in the dialogue D, which is the following string: A: Drive slowly, David. You could have an accident. 
<utt> B: You can count on me. I have been driving for years. <utt> A: Look out! Red light! <utt> B: It doesn't 
matter. It is late. There is no one around. <utt> A: Don't let the police catch you. Oh, David, that's a policeman. 
He is waving over us.
